name: Dummy
summary: It's a dummy, dummy.

name: Kitnip
summary: Many trainers who don't like to battle still keep Kitnip as a companion due to its extreme cuteness.  It likes to chase the bud on its tail when it gets bored.

name: Dandylion
summary: It looks fearsome, but in the wrong wind its own seeds can cause it to sneeze uncontrollably. Unlike its namesake, it gets most of its energy from photosynthesis.

name: Emperoar
summary: An extremely loyal MegaBit, Emperoar has been known to offer its leaves (which can be used to make a potent healing tea) to sick MegaBits and trainers.

name: Embrant
summary: It is docile as long as it is not upset. Unfortunately, it is easily startled due to its excellent hearing. The flame on its tail flares when it is about to lash out.

name: Vertusk
summary: Much larger and more confident than its first evolution, Vertusk responds to threats by putting them to sleep instead of lashing out with fire attacks.

name: Olifire
summary: One of the largest known MegaBits, Olifire is gentle unless angered. An enraged Olifire is capable of single-handedly destroying entire neighborhoods with its fire.

name: Happop
summary: It is very trusting and friendly and can't move very fast. The shell fragment on its head helps to protect it when it's forced into battle.

name: Hippajet
summary: Has a strong sense of right and wrong. Likes to help other MegaBits and humans, especially by fighting fires. Its can-do attitude sometimes gets it into trouble.

name: Hippotora
summary: The combination of extreme aggression, huge size, and surprising speed makes it extremely dangerous. It prefers to fight truly challenging opponents.

name: Zapoink
summary: The strength of its electrical output depends on its emotional state. When it feels safe and content, the plasma globe on its tail can light a whole room.

name: Watthog
summary: The plasma globe on its tail is no longer able to contain its power. Watthog is constantly surrounded by arcs of electricity, badly shocking anyone who grabs its tail.

name: Tuskla
summary: This MegaBit stores huge amounts of electrical energy. Even when it's relaxed, petting its fur can result in a jolt hefty enough to knock out an adult human.

name: Charpal
summary: When it runs through tall grass, its fiery tale can leave flames in its wake. Researchers now believe it to have caused several previously unexplained wildfires.

name: Charrid
summary: Capable of running as fast as a car. It is willing to take on any foe to protect its young. The flames on its back plate erupt like a volcano when it gets angry.

name: Piripine
summary: When threatened, it curls up into a protective ball. Anything that attacks Piripine in its curled-up state gets a mouthful of spiky, poisonous burs.

name: Burbilla
summary: Despite its short legs and stocky build, it is can run up to 30 kph over short distances. It is sometimes called the "spiny badger".

name: Bunbun
summary: One of the most common MegaBits, and thus one of the very first MegaBits to be discovered. Rubbing the small rounded horns on its head is said to bring good luck.

name: Ovol
summary: It prefers to spend most of its time flying, as it has a hard time balancing its spherical body on a perch. The hooting call of an Ovol in the night can be very unsettling.

name: Elecdrone
summary: When many Elecdrones gather in one place, often around power lines, they produce the buzzing, humming sound that many people attribute to high-voltage lines.

name: Pluridrone
summary: They tend to live in high, remote places. When lightning strikes twice in the same place, it is often because of the strong electrical field produced by a Pluridrone.

name: Matottle
summary: Despite its resemblance to the koala, it is native to the temperate rainforests of the Pacific Northwest, where it spends most of its time in the canopy.

name: Ursylva
summary: Extremely rare. Researchers have tied them to Native American legends of forest guardians. They seem to actively dislike humans.

name: Steellig
summary: It spends a great deal of time standing around doing nothing. In this way, it saves up a great deal of energy for its next stage of evolution.

name: Rustik
summary: It is believed to feed on untreated metal, leaving rust in its wake. It is very shy and has been known to jump up to 10 meters when it feels threatened.

name: Circada
summary: Its eyes look red when they reflect light. It likes to live near old factories. Some researchers believe that it may have been responsible for the "Mothman" sightings.

name: Grimlug
summary: Unlike most MegaBits, it is known to eat carrion as well as leaves and berries. It is extremely haughty and has been known to attack disrespectful trainers without warning.

name: Grimard
summary: Its silvery eyes have been said to take control of people who stare into them for too long. The marks on its back mirror the constellations of the night sky.

name: Mytox
summary: It appears at night in warm, moist areas. Its arms are almost useless, since they are too short to reach anything beyond the edge of its cap. Its spores cause hallucinations.

name: Parafur
summary: The shell Parafur wears on its head doesn't belong to any known species of turtle; some scientists think it may come from another MegaBit. Parafur is usually very shy.

name: Donafur
summary: The scientist who first discovered it called it "an otter on a half shell". It is very confident and likes to test itself against other MegaBits at every opportunity.

name: Gorafur
summary: Gorafur's shell is fused to its body and grows with it.  Gorafur is very serious, and has been known to lead groups of Donafur and Parafur into battle when their habitat is threatened.

name: Cragry
summary: No matter how adorable Cragry is, never pet one. Its white fur is cold enough to cause frostbite and its darker fur is hot enough to cause burns.

name: Arcturupt
summary: The arctic volcano MegaBit. Because it is both very hot and very cold at the same time, it is always in a foul mood. It will attack Cragatoa and Koldiak on sight.

name: Cragatoa
summary: Cragatoa contains an immense amount of heat, and because of this heat it constantly glows. When it becomes angry, the air around its body superheats and can cause nearby trees to burst into flame.

name: Koldiak
summary: The ice that covers its head and forelegs is so deeply frozen that it is comparable in strength to diamonds. Its claws are essentially unbreakable.

name: Vocifer
summary: Incredibly rare. It is known primarily by the effects its screams can have on MegaBits a mile or more away. Almost nothing else is known about it.

name: Psylapod
summary: Extremely rare. Its body is almost entirely made up of water telekinetically controlled by the brain coral within. It is capable of psychically manipulating almost anything.
